#. <section class="sutta" id="sn54.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn54.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 54"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 54"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn54.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Ekadhammavagga"
msgstr "1. One Thing"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Mahākappinasutta → kappinasuttaṃ (bj) | kappino (pts1)
msgctxt "sn54.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Mahākappinasutta"
msgstr "7. About Mahākappina"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn54.7:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā mahākappino bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti "
"pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"Now, at that time Venerable Mahākappino was sitting not far from the Buddha "
"cross-legged, with his body straight, and mindfulness established right "
"there."

msgctxt "sn54.7:1.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahākappinaṃ avidūre nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ "
"ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr "The Buddha saw him,"

msgctxt "sn54.7:1.4"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.316"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.7:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etassa bhikkhuno kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā "
"phanditattaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, do you see any motion or trembling in that mendicant’s body?”"

msgctxt "sn54.7:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Yadāpi mayaṃ, bhante, taṃ āyasmantaṃ passāma saṅghamajjhe vā nisinnaṃ ekaṃ "
"vā raho nisinnaṃ, tadāpi mayaṃ tassa āyasmato na passāma kāyassa iñjitattaṃ "
"vā phanditattaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, whenever we see that mendicant meditating—whether in the middle of the "
"Saṅgha or alone in private—we never see any motion or trembling in his body.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.7:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yassa, bhikkhave, samādhissa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa "
"iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti "
"phanditattaṃ vā, tassa so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samādhissa nikāmalābhī "
"akicchalābhī akasiralābhī."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when an immersion has been developed and cultivated there’s no "
"motion or trembling of the body or mind. That mendicant gets such immersion "
"when he wants, without trouble or difficulty."

msgctxt "sn54.7:3.2"
msgid ""
"Katamassa ca, bhikkhave, samādhissa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa "
"iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti "
"phanditattaṃ vā?"
msgstr "And what is that immersion?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.7:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ānāpānassatisamādhissa, bhikkhave, bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa "
"iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti "
"phanditattaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"When immersion due to mindfulness of breathing has been developed and "
"cultivated there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind."

msgctxt "sn54.7:4.2"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvite ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi kathaṃ bahulīkate neva "
"kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti "
"phanditattaṃ vā?"
msgstr ""
"And how is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and "
"cultivated in such a way?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.7:5.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā "
"nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ "
"upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to "
"an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and "
"establishes their mindfulness right there."

msgctxt "sn54.7:5.2"
msgid "So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …"
msgstr "Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …"

msgctxt "sn54.7:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They "
"practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’"

msgctxt "sn54.7:5.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvite ca kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi evaṃ bahulīkate neva "
"kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti "
"phanditattaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and "
"cultivated so that there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn54.7:5.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
